@node using "Using ClassAction"


    @{b}Using ClassAction@{ub}


    Using ClassAction is simple. If you do not know what button is for which
    purpose, just move the mouse over it and read the hint at the bottom.

    Start the preference program by selecting 'Preferences' from the main menu.
    To quit, just click on the Close icon or select 'Quit' from the main menu.

    @{b}Main menu@{ub}

    The right mouse button (RMB) opens the @{" main menu " link menu} if you are
    not over the lister or special buttons. You can choose one of many commands,
    related to the program, the view, the current options and more.

    @{b}Listers@{ub}

    The filemanager works like all the other known managers:
    there's always an active (or source-) lister, indicated by a green lamp at
    the right of its path. The other lister is always the destination. All
    actions will use this fact except special actions defined by you ! (There is
    a parameter you can use to specify the lister your action will work on, and
    variables that indicate source and destination path.)

    In the DirLists you can move as in a normal file requester.
    Left to the path string there is an arrow which leads to the parent
    directory. The next button is for refreshing the display if some files or
    dirs have changed. Click on the column titles to sort by suffix, name, size
    or date.

    Pressing a key will show the 1st file starting with this letter, and
    Shift+Key will does the same for directories.
    (This can be overwritten by your own commands that could for example copy
    the selected files by pressing "c".)

    @{b}File operations@{ub}

    After you have selected one or more files in the lister, you can press the
    RMB and you will see the file class and the corresponding defined actions.
    Just select the action you want.

    If you double-click on a file, the first defined action will be launched.
    If you click on the size entry of a directory, ClassAction will count the
    bytes in this directory and show it.
    Last but not least you can open an information requester for a file by a
    double-click on the date or protection bits. Here you can change the file's
    attributes and get its version if available.


    @{b}Popup menus@{ub}

    A click on the right mouse button opens one of the @{b}popup menus@{ub},
    depending on the mouse positions:

    the first appears above the arrow and shows the paths you have already
    visited (the lister history).
    The second belongs to the refresh button and contains all volumes that can
    be listed.
    The third opens at the path edit field and shows a set of defined paths that
    you can change yourself in the preferences.
    The last is the directory menu, it contains some often used functions for
    the active directory. You can open it on the lamp right to the path.

    @{b}Buttons and keys@{ub}

    Special actions are available through the
    @{" buttons at the top and bottom " link buttons}.
    Some of these methods can be accessed by keys; the keys are defined with
    ClassActionPrefs and can be viewed and changed. In the standard setting, you
    can for example delete the selected files by DEL. HELP will always show this
    manual.
    See @{" keys " link keys} for a complete description of the predefined
    key shortcuts.

    @{b}Additional Features@{ub}

    The ClassAction window is an AppWindow, thus you can throw icons on the main
    window. Drop a drawer into ClassAction to list its contents; you can do this
    in the left or right lister. Or drop a file and you'll get the popup menu
    with the file specific actions. Try and enjoy !

    To transform the window into an AppIcon just choose the iconify icon or
    choose 'iconify' from the main menu. Double click on the AppIcon to reopen
    the window.

    When ClassAction is iconified, you can throw icons on it like into the
    window. As only difference, you'll get also a popup menu for drawers.

    If you can't see ClassAction, press CTRL-ALT-F1 (or the key you defined in
    ClassActionPrefs) to bring it to the front, or CTRL-ALT-F2 to iconify it.
    You can also do this with commodity control programs like Exchange or
    MRE StartMenu.


    See also

    @{" ARexx Commands " link arexx}
    @{" Buttons        " link buttons}
    @{" Configuration  " link cap}
    @{" Menu           " link menu}

@endnode

@node buttons "The Buttons"

    This is a list of predefined commands. You can change them and
    create new ones with @{" ClassActionPrefs " link commands}.

    @{b}Selection Buttons @{ub}

    On top of the source lister there are 6 buttons that make
    selection easier:

    All:     Select all entries in the lister, even directories.
    None:    Deselect all entries.
    Pattern: Select all files that match the pattern you enter.
             Directories will @{b}not@{ub} be selected.
    Type:    Select all files of the same class as the selected one.
             Directories will @{b}not@{ub} be selected.
    Toggle:  Switch selected/unselected entries.
             Affects also directories.
    GetSize: Compute and show the size of all selected files and
             directories.
    Swap:    Swap the contents of the source and destination lister.


    @{b}Directory Buttons @{ub}

    For both listers there are buttons to move inside and create
    new drawers:

    Devices: Show volumes and assigns.
    MakeDir: Create a new directory; you will be asked for its name.
             If the option 'CreateIcons' is turned on, also an icon
             is created.

    @{b}Action Buttons @{ub}

    Some actions can be executed on the selected files directly by
    these buttons:

    WbInfo:  Show the Workbench icon information of the selected files.
             There you can modify file attributes and edit the icon.
    AddIcon: Create an icon for the selected files.
             If there already exists an icon you will be informed, and
             nothing will happen.
    Rename:  Rename the selected files.
    Delete:  Delete the selected files. You will be asked if you
             really want it.

    @{b}Transfer Buttons @{ub}

    You can transfer files with the aid of following buttons:

    Copy:    Copy the selected files to the destination directory.
    CopyAs:  Copy the selected files to the destination directory, and
             give them the name you enter.
    Move:    Move the selected files to the destination directory.
    MoveAs:  Move the selected files to the destination directory, and
             give them the name you enter.

    @{b}Other buttons @{ub}

    There can be other buttons to show the possibilities. Look into
    the preferences to get more information about the commands.


    See also

    @{" ClassActionPrefs " link cap}
    @{" Commands         " link commands}
@endnode

@node menu "The Menu"

    The most menu items are internal commands. Look into their
    @{" description " link internalcom} to know what they do.

    @{b}Project@{ub}

    Help:        See HELP
    Preferences: See PREFS
    About:       See ABOUT
    Iconify:     See ICONIFY
    Quit:        See QUIT

    @{b}Edit@{b}

    Copy:             See CLIPCOPY
    Paste:            See CLIPPASTE
    Select all:       See ALL
    Select nothing:   See NONE
    Select pattern:   See PATTERN
    Toggle selection: See TOGGLE
    Select same type: See TYPE
    Search:           See SEARCH

    @{b}Settings@{ub}

    Snapshot Window: Save the current window position and size.
                     The next time ClassAction starts it will use these
                     dimensions. You can also specify exact values
                     in @{" ClassActionPrefs " link cap}.

    The following options are identically to the @{" options " link options}
    with the same name.
    So if you want to change one of the options permanently, you have
    to change the @{" preferences " link options}.


    See also

    @{" Internal commands " link internalcom}
@endnode

@node keys "The Keys"


    @{b}The Keys@{ub}


    Many ClassAction functions can be accessed by shortcuts. Define own
    key commands in ClassActionPrefs if you want to have more or other
    keys.
    The F keys are comparable to those of the WindowsCommander to make
    life easier for Windows users.

    @{b}General@{ub}

    BACKSPACE           Go to the parent directory
    SHIFT BACKSPACE     Go to the root directory
    ALT   BACKSPACE     Show the volumes/assigns
    DEL                 Delete selected files
    RETURN              Start action/enter directory (like a double click)
    ENTER               Show the file popup menu (like right mouse button)
    SPACE               Activate the path edit field of the current lister
    TAB                 Switch active lister
    F1 or HELP          Show this manual
    F2                  Refresh the current lister

    The following keys are part of the ClassAction commodity; you don't have to
    activate the ClassAction window to use them:

    CTRL ALT F1         Show ClassAction window
    CTRL ALT F2         Iconify ClassAction window

    @{b}View@{ub}

    CURSORLEFT          Shift list browser to the left
    ALT CURSORLEFT      Show right dir in the left browser
    CURSORRIGHT         Shift list browser to the right
    ALT CURSORRIGHT     Show left dir in the right browser
    CURSORUP            Shift list browser up
    SHIFT CURSORUP      Shift list browser one page up
    CTRL  CURSORUP      Show start of the list
    CURSORDOWN          Shift list browser down
    SHIFT CURSORDOWN    Shift list browser one page down
    CTRL  CURSORDOWN    Show end of the list

    @{b}Selection@{ub}

    All these keys are accessable through the NUMBLOCK and change the file
    selection:

    1           Select the last file
    2           Select the next file
    3           Select the file one page down
    4           Go to the parent directory
    5,6         Start action/enter directory (like a double click)
    7           Select the first file
    8           Select the next file
    9           Select the file one page up

    @{b}File operations@{ub}

    Standard actions like copy, rename etc. are on F keys:

    F3          Open selected files with multiview ("View")
    F4          Open selected files with ed        ("Edit")
    F5          Copy selected files
    SHIFT F5    Copy and rename selected files
    ALT   F5    Duplicate selected files
    F6          Move selected files
    SHIFT F6    Move and rename selected files
    F7          Create a directory
    F8          Delete selected files
    SHIFT F8    Move selected files to trashcan
    F9          Rename selected files



    @{b}Summary@{ub}

    BACKSPACE           Go to the parent directory
    BACKSPACE + SHIFT   Go to the root directory
    BACKSPACE + ALT     Show the volumes/assigns
    CURSORLEFT          Shift list browser to the left
    CURSORLEFT + ALT    Show right dir in the left browser
    CURSORRIGHT         Shift list browser to the right
    CURSORRIGHT + ALT   Show left dir in the right browser
    CURSORUP            Shift list browser up
    CURSORUP + SHIFT    Shift list browser one page up
    CURSORUP + CTRL     Show start of the list
    CURSORDOWN          Shift list browser down
    CURSORDOWN + SHIFT  Shift list browser one page down
    CURSORDOWN + CTRL   Show end of the list
    DEL                 Delete selected files
    ENTER               Show the file popup menu (like right mouse button)
    F1                  Show this manual
    F1 + CTRL ALT       Show ClassAction window
    F2                  Refresh the current lister
    F2 + CTRL ALT       Iconify ClassAction window
    F3                  Open selected files with multiview ("View")
    F4                  Open selected files with ed        ("Edit")
    F5                  Copy selected files
    F5 + SHIFT          Copy and rename selected files
    F5 + ALT            Duplicate selected files
    F6                  Move selected files
    F6 + SHIFT          Move and rename selected files
    F7                  Create a directory
    F8                  Delete selected files
    F8 + SHIFT          Move selected files to trashcan
    F9                  Rename selected files
    HELP                Show this manual
    NUMBLOCK 1          Select the last file
    NUMBLOCK 2          Select the next file
    NUMBLOCK 3          Select the file one page down
    NUMBLOCK 4          Go to the parent directory
    NUMBLOCK 5,6        Start action/enter directory (like a double click)
    NUMBLOCK 7          Select the first file
    NUMBLOCK 8          Select the next file
    NUMBLOCK 9          Select the file one page up
    RETURN              Start action/enter directory (like a double click)
    SPACE               Activate the path edit field of the current lister
    TAB                 Switch active lister


    In addition, the most items of the main menu possess shortcuts. They
    depend on the language you use, so please have a look at your main menu
    to know the keys you need.


    See also

    @{" Internal commands " link commands}

@endnode

@node infotech "Technicals Infos"


    @{b}Technicals Infos@{ub}


    ClassAction was first coded with DICE C 3.0 and is now developped in C++
    with StormC 3.0, using ReAction (nice name ;-).
    It's real C++ with some nice classes for ARexx, the menu, the preference
    files, ... Contact the author if you want to look into the source code.

    Miscelleaneous info :

    The prefs file is an ASCII file named ENVARC:ClassAction.prefs

    Disk libraries required :

        popupmenu.library

    Disk libraries used if found :

        xadmaster.library (SHAREWARE!!)


    How ClassAction determines a class :

        1- test if it's a volume, assign or directory
        2- test if the filename matches the pattern of a defined class.
        3- test if the file matches the offsets of a defined class.
        4- test if the file is ASCII (if ASCII Offset Command exists)

        If everything fails, the file is declared as 'Unknown Class'.

@endnode


@node Install "Installation"


    @{b}Installing@{ub}


    Use the installer script given with the archive.
    To use it, just click on the install icon.

    ClassAction requires the MRE: assign. This will be set by the installer
    script.

    The following files are copied (with their icons if available):

    ClassAction         to MRE:executables
    ClassActionPrefs    to SYS:Prefs
    ClassAction.guide   to HELP:
    ClassAction.prefs   to ENVARC:

    and some internal files to the related drawers in MRE:


    See also

    @{" After Install " link after}

@endnode

